<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">schools</ENAMEX> just as he envisions doing nationally. <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Students</ENAMEX> have to take the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Texas</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Assessment of Academic</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">Skills</ENAMEX> (TAAS). On the basis of that test and a few other
factors, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">schools</ENAMEX> are rated in one of <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">four</NUMEX> categories: "low-performing,"
"acceptable," "recognized," or "exemplary." <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">Only one</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">school</ENAMEX> in the entire
state--<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Goodrich Elementary School</ENAMEX>, <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">60 miles</NUMEX> outside <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Houston</ENAMEX>--has been rated
